article.headline: Youngstown St. 77, Slippery Rock 63
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Byron Davis scored 15 points to lead three double-digit scorers as Youngstown State beat Slippery Rock 77-63 on Saturday. Starting the second half after a first-half tie at 38 a piece, Youngstown State went on a nine-point run and never looked back. Vytas Sulskis drained two three pointers in the first minute after halftime to add 6 points for Youngstown State (4-7) and Dwight Holmes and Davis added three more before the Rock scored for the first time in the second half. John Barber had 13 points for the Penguins and Sulskis added 12. Neither team shot very well. Division II Slippery Rock shot only 37 percent (23-of-62) while Youngstown State shot only marginally better at 39 percent (25-of-64). The Penguins out-rebounded the Rock 49-39. Ken Ottrix led Slippery Rock (2-9) with 18 points and nine rebounds. Matt Schaefer had 16 and Cory Somerville had 12.
